scout
=====
scout is an extremely fast, small, and dynamic file manager.


Requirements
------------
In order to build scout you need the ncurses header files.


Installation
------------
Edit config.mk to match your local setup (scout is installed into
the /usr/local namespace by default).

Afterwards enter the following command to build and install scout
(if necessary as root):

    make clean install


Running scout
-------------
Usage: scout [path]
       -v version
       -h help


Configuration
-------------
The configuration of scout is done by creating a custom config.h
and (re)compiling the source code.
